t-->\n\n'''''East of Midnight''''' is [[Canada|Canadian]] musician [[Gordon Lightfoot]]'s 17th original album, released in 1986 on the [[Warner Bros. Records]] label. The album reached #165 on the [[Billboard magazine|Billboard 200]].\n\nLightfoot enlisted [[Keyboard instrument|keyboardist]] and producer [[David Foster]] on the song \"Anything for Love\", which reached #13 on the Adult Contemporary chart and #71 on the [[Country music|Country]] chart.\n\n==Track listing==\nAll compositions by Lightfoot except as indicated.\n#\"Stay Loose\" \u2013 3:53\n#\"Morning Glory\" \u2013 3:24\n#\"East of Midnight\" \u2013 3:58\n#\"A Lesson in Love\" \u2013 4:05\n#\"Anything for Love\" \u2013 3:43 (Lightfoot, [[David Foster]])\n#\"Let it Ride\" \u2013 3:40\n#\"Ecstasy Made Easy\" \u2013 4:05\n#\"You Just Gotta Be\" \u2013 3:34\n#\"A Passing Ship\" \u2013 3:55\n#\"I'll Tag Along\" \u2013 3:08\n\n== Personnel ==\n* Gordon Lightfoot - main vocals, [[guitar]] \n* [[Lenny Castro]] - [[Percussion instrument|percussion]] \n* Vern Dorge - [[alto saxophone]], [[tenor saxophone]] \n* [[David Foster]] - [[synthesizer]], [[Keyboard instrument|keyboards]]\n* Mike Heffernan - keyboards \n* [[James Newton Howard]] - synthesizer, percussion, keyboards \n* Sheree Jeacocke - harmony vocals \n* Barry Keane - percussion, [[drum]]s \n* [[Michael Landau]] - guitar \n* Bob Mann - Guitar, [[rhythm guitar]] \n* [[Richard Marx]] - harmony vocals \n* Lou Pomanti - [[Hammond organ]] \n* Tom Szczesniak - synthesizer, [[Bass guitar|bass]], keyboards \n* [[Vesta Williams]] - harmony vocals\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.lightfoot.ca/eastlist.htm Album lyrics and chords]\n\n{{Lightfoot}}\n\n[[Category:1986 albums]]\n[[Category:Gordon Lightfoot albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by David Foster]]\n[[Category:Warner Records albums]]\n", "name_user": "WBH", "label": "safe", "comment": "adding URL of review", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/East_of_Midnight"}
